-- 02_active_subscriptions.sql
```sql
WITH deduplicated_billing AS (
  SELECT DISTINCT ON (subscription_id, event_month)
    subscription_id,
    event_month,
    amount,
    event_type
  FROM billing_events
),
active_subs AS (
  SELECT 
    s.subscription_id,
    s.user_id,
    p.tier,
    c.industry,
    db.event_month,
    db.amount
  FROM subscriptions s
  LEFT JOIN plans p ON s.plan_id = p.plan_id
  LEFT JOIN users u ON s.user_id = u.user_id
  LEFT JOIN companies c ON u.company_id = c.company_id
  INNER JOIN deduplicated_billing db ON s.subscription_id = db.subscription_id
  WHERE s.status = 'active'
)
```

-- 03_monthly_metrics.sql
```sql
WITH deduplicated_billing AS (
  SELECT DISTINCT ON (subscription_id, event_month)
    subscription_id,
    event_month,
    amount,
    event_type
  FROM billing_events
),
active_subs AS (
  SELECT 
    s.subscription_id,
    s.user_id,
    COALESCE(p.tier, 'Unknown') AS tier,
    COALESCE(c.industry, 'Unknown') AS industry,
    db.event_month,
    db.amount
  FROM subscriptions s
  LEFT JOIN plans p ON s.plan_id = p.plan_id
  LEFT JOIN users u ON s.user_id = u.user_id
  LEFT JOIN companies c ON u.company_id = c.company_id
  INNER JOIN deduplicated_billing db ON s.subscription_id = db.subscription_id
  WHERE s.status = 'active'
)
SELECT
  event_month AS month,
  tier,
  industry,
  COUNT(DISTINCT subscription_id) AS active_subscriptions,
  SUM(amount) AS total_mrr,
  COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) AS unique_users
FROM active_subs
GROUP BY event_month, tier, industry
ORDER BY event_month, tier, industry;
